Source-Makefile: feeds/packages/lang/golang/golang1.26/Makefile
Build-Depends: golang1.26/host
Build-Depends/host: golang-bootstrap/host
Build-Types: host

Package: golang1.26
Submenu: Go
Version: 1.26.1-r1
Depends: +libc @(aarch64||arm||i386||i686||loongarch64||mips||mips64||mips64el||mipsel||riscv64||x86_64) +golang1.26-src
Conflicts: 
Menu-Depends: +golang-bootstrap
Provides: @golang1.26-any @golang
Section: lang
Category: Languages
Repository: base
Title: Go programming language (compiler)
Maintainer: George Sapkin <george@sapk.in>
Source: go1.26.1.src.tar.gz
License: BSD-3-Clause
LicenseFiles: LICENSE
CPE-ID: cpe:/a:golang:go
URL: https://go.dev/
Type: ipkg
Description:     The Go programming language is an open source project to make programmers more
  productive.

  Go is expressive, concise, clean, and efficient. Its concurrency mechanisms
  make it easy to write programs that get the most out of multi-core and
  networked machines, while its novel type system enables flexible and modular
  program construction. Go compiles quickly to machine code yet has the
  convenience of garbage collection and the power of run-time reflection. It's
  a fast, statically typed, compiled language that feels like a dynamically
  typed, interpreted language.

  This package provides an assembler, compiler, linker, and compiled libraries
  for the Go programming language.
@@

